---
import Docs from '../../layouts/Docs.astro';
import { keys } from '../../lib/keybindings';

const toc = [
  { id: 'first-launch', text: 'First Launch', level: 2 },
  { id: 'essential-shortcuts', text: 'Essential Shortcuts', level: 2 },
  { id: 'splits', text: 'Your First Split', level: 2 },
  { id: 'tabs', text: 'Tabs', level: 2 },
  { id: 'font-size', text: 'Font Size', level: 2 },
  { id: 'search', text: 'Search', level: 2 },
  { id: 'copy-paste', text: 'Copy & Paste', level: 2 },
  { id: 'next-steps', text: 'Next Steps', level: 2 },
];
---

<Docs title="Quick Start" toc={toc}>
  <h2 id="first-launch">First Launch</h2>
  <p>Run <code>ori-term</code> from your existing terminal or application launcher. ori-term starts with your default shell and a single pane. No configuration file is required — sensible defaults are built in.</p>
  <p>You'll see a frameless window with a tab bar at the top and your shell prompt. Everything works out of the box.</p>

  <h2 id="essential-shortcuts">Essential Shortcuts</h2>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Action</th>
        <th>Shortcut</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td>New tab</td><td><kbd>{keys.newTab}</kbd></td></tr>
      <tr><td>Close pane/tab</td><td><kbd>{keys.closePane}</kbd></td></tr>
      <tr><td>Split right</td><td><kbd>{keys.splitRight}</kbd></td></tr>
      <tr><td>Split down</td><td><kbd>{keys.splitDown}</kbd></td></tr>
      <tr><td>Focus pane</td><td><kbd>{keys.focusPaneDir}</kbd></td></tr>
      <tr><td>Next tab</td><td><kbd>{keys.nextTab}</kbd></td></tr>
      <tr><td>Previous tab</td><td><kbd>{keys.prevTab}</kbd></td></tr>
      <tr><td>Search</td><td><kbd>{keys.openSearch}</kbd></td></tr>
      <tr><td>Font larger</td><td><kbd>{keys.fontLarger}</kbd></td></tr>
      <tr><td>Font smaller</td><td><kbd>{keys.fontSmaller}</kbd></td></tr>
      <tr><td>Reload config</td><td><kbd>{keys.reloadConfig}</kbd></td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
  <p>See <a href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/$/, '')}/docs/keybindings`}>Keybindings</a> for the complete reference.</p>

  <h2 id="splits">Your First Split</h2>
  <p>Press <kbd>{keys.splitRight}</kbd> to split the current pane to the right. You now have two panes side by side, each running your shell. Navigate between them with <kbd>{keys.focusLeft}</kbd> and <kbd>{keys.focusRight}</kbd>.</p>
  <p>Press <kbd>{keys.splitDown}</kbd> to split down. Resize with <kbd>{keys.resizePane}</kbd>. Close a pane with <kbd>{keys.closePane}</kbd> — the remaining panes expand to fill the space.</p>

  <h2 id="tabs">Tabs</h2>
  <p>Press <kbd>{keys.newTab}</kbd> for a new tab. Each tab has its own split tree. Switch between tabs with <kbd>{keys.nextTab}</kbd> and <kbd>{keys.prevTab}</kbd>, or click the tab bar.</p>
  <p>Accidentally closed a tab? <kbd>{keys.undoCloseTab}</kbd> restores it with the working directory preserved.</p>

  <h2 id="font-size">Font Size</h2>
  <p>Adjust on the fly with <kbd>{keys.fontLarger}</kbd> to increase and <kbd>{keys.fontSmaller}</kbd> to decrease. The terminal reflows content to fit the new cell size.</p>

  <h2 id="search">Search</h2>
  <p><kbd>{keys.openSearch}</kbd> opens the search bar. Type your query and matches highlight across the viewport and scrollback. Press <kbd>{keys.nextMatch}</kbd> to jump to the next match, <kbd>{keys.prevMatch}</kbd> for previous. <kbd>{keys.closeSearch}</kbd> to close.</p>

  <h2 id="copy-paste">Copy & Paste</h2>
  <p>Select text by clicking and dragging. Double-click to select a word, triple-click for a line. Copy with <kbd>{keys.copy}</kbd> (or enable copy-on-select in config). Paste with <kbd>{keys.paste}</kbd>.</p>

  <h2 id="next-steps">Next Steps</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><a href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/$/, '')}/docs/configuration`}>Configuration</a> — Customize ori-term to your preferences</li>
    <li><a href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/$/, '')}/docs/keybindings`}>Keybindings</a> — Full shortcut reference</li>
    <li><a href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/$/, '')}/docs/panes`}>Panes & Splits</a> — Advanced pane management</li>
    <li><a href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/$/, '')}/docs/theming`}>Theming</a> — Choose or create your color scheme</li>
  </ul>
</Docs>
